// Custom attributes
include::common/attributes/cfme.adoc[]

:cfme:

:numbered:

You can assign different analysis profiles for specific virtual machine configurations or purposes using the Red Hat CloudForms user interface. The procedure consists of creating a custom virtual machine analysis profile and assigning it to a virtual machine via a control policy.

This document describes the following steps required to assign a custom analysis profile to a virtual machine for use with smart state analysis.

. Creating a Virtual Machine Analysis Profile
. Adding an Assign Profile to Analysis Task Action
. Creating a Virtual Machine Control Policy
. Creating a Policy Profile and Assigning the Virtual Machine Control Policy
. Assigning the Policy Profile to a Virtual Machine


